  "content:encoded": "<p>In this episode, I review some feed back from you, the good listener, before getting into the interview with Lieutenant-Colonel Cliff Trollope. LCol Trollope served for the majority of his military career with the <a title=\"PPCLI.com\" href=\"http://www.ppcli.com\">Princess Patricia&#8217;s Canadian Light Infantry</a>. He began his service at the <a title=\"Royal Military College\" href=\"http://www.rmc.ca/\">Royal Military College</a> and also was an instructor at the Infantry School in <a title=\"Infantry School\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combat_Training_Centre\">Gagetown</a>, New Brunswick. He concluded his military service as the Commanding Officer of the <a title=\"The Royal Regiment of Canada\" href=\"http://www.theroyalregimentofcanada.org/\">Royal Regiment of Canada</a>, where he lead the Regiment through their period of providing individual augmentation to the <a title=\"Canadian Mission in Afghanistan\" href=\"http://www.afghanistan.gc.ca/canada-afghanistan/index.aspx\">mission in Afghanistan</a> and the presentation and consecration of the Colours by <a title=\"The Prince of Wales\" href=\"http://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/\">HRH, the Prince of Wales</a>.</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-110-66\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-005-LCol-Cliff-Trollope.mp3?_=66\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-005-LCol-Cliff-Trollope.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-005-LCol-Cliff-Trollope.mp3</a></audio>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/DSC_1922.bmp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\" wp-image-112 aligncenter\" title=\"LCol Cliff Trollope CD, Commanding Officer of the Roya Regiment of Canada\" alt=\"DSC_1922\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/DSC_1922.bmp\" width=\"319\" height=\"480\" /></a>Lieutenant-Colonel Cliff Trollope, Commanding Officer of the Royal Regiment of Canada</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/12-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours-sm.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-113 aligncenter\" alt=\"12-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours-sm\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/12-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours-sm-300x171.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/12-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours-sm-300x171.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/12-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours-sm.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>  LCol Trollope escorting HRH Charles, The Prince of Wales during the presentation and consecration of Colours to the Royal Regiment of Canada and the Toronto Scottish Regiment</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/13-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours2-sm.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-114 aligncenter\" alt=\"13-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours2-sm\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/13-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours2-sm-300x114.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"114\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/13-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours2-sm-300x114.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/13-Royal-Visit-2009-Nov-Charles-Regt-colours2-sm.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/4089906067_8e4c4c49f1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-115 alignleft\" alt=\"Britain's Prince Charles inspects the Royal Regiment of Canada in Toronto\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/4089906067_8e4c4c49f1-300x193.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/4089906067_8e4c4c49f1-300x193.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/4089906067_8e4c4c49f1.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-119 alignright\" alt=\"Trollope2\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope2-300x237.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope2-300x237.png 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope2.png 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Trollope1\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Trollope1-190x300.png\" width=\"190\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Leading soldiers on operations</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-117\" alt=\"Divine Service\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/IMG_0166-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/IMG_0166-300x200.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/IMG_0166.jpg 720w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">LCol Trollope on parade at Fort York Armoury &#8211; Is this a good time for some push-ups?!?</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"CMHP Logo1400x1400\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400-300x300.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n",
